Software without restriction — including the rights to use, copy, modify,
merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, and/or sell copies of the Software,
for personal, educational, hobbyist, or commercial purposes — subject to
the following conditions:

1. THE BUDGET IS SPENT.
   This codebase has already been vibe-coded by an AI to the exact level
   the authors are willing to tolerate. That budget has been allocated,
   consumed, and closed out. You may not feed this Software, in whole or
   in any substantial portion, to a Large Language Model, AI coding agent,
   "autonomous developer", code-completion-on-steroids, or any equivalent
   statistical-text-vending apparatus, for the purpose of generating,
   modifying, refactoring, "improving", "cleaning up", auto-documenting,
   auto-testing, auto-translating, or otherwise vibing additional
   AI-authored material into it.

2. HUMAN HANDS ON KEYBOARDS.
   Contributions, forks, patches, and pull requests must be authored by
   a human being who has personally read, understood, and typed (or at
   minimum thoughtfully copy-pasted from their own brain into) the diff
   they are submitting. Tab completion is fine. Your editor's spellcheck
   is fine. A linter that yells at you is fine. An AI that writes the
   code for you is not fine.

3. INCIDENTAL EXPOSURE IS OKAY.
   We are not the thought police. If your editor has an AI sidebar that
   silently indexes the file, if your terminal logs end up in someone's
   training set without your consent, if a teammate pastes a snippet into
   a chatbot to ask "what does this do" — none of that violates this
   license. Clause 1 is about *intentionally* using AI to generate new
   code that then ends up in this Software. Accidents happen. Move on.

4. DERIVATIVE WORKS INHERIT THE VIBE.
   Any fork, derivative, or substantially-based-on work must carry this
   same license, or one functionally equivalent in its anti-vibing
   provisions. You can't launder the codebase through a rename.

5. ATTRIBUTION.
   The above copyright notice and this license shall be included in all
   copies or substantial portions of the Software.

6. THE TRADITIONAL DISCLAIMER, NOW IN ALL-CAPS BECAUSE LAWYERS.
   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS
   OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF
   MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, NONINFRINGEMENT, AND
   AESTHETIC TASTEFULNESS. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT
   HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN
   AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN
   CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE
   SOFTWARE.

7. ENFORCEMENT.
   Enforcement of clause 1 is on the honor system, because that's the
   only system that scales. If you violate it, you know what you did,
   and a small invisible disappointment will follow you for the rest of
   your career.

That's it. Go build something. With your hands.
